{
  "doc_id": "42521",
  "text": "As mentioned previously, the CMOS sensor delivers information as a Bayer array with raw data and the size of n x m. The Bayer array consists of three color components: green, red and blue; it applies to this information an algorithm of color interpolation or rebuilding, which is a digital process used to reconstruct an image to the RGB color model from samples acquired from the multispectral CMOS image sensor [CITATION_1] .",
